cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.IT

The paper deals with approximate Bayesian inference in log-supermodular models, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of submodular minimization, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
